<subSubSection id="808E6553DC12FF15FF2F1C97FFCDDB92" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="C82B36D8DC12FF15FF2F1C97FFCDDB92" blockId="1.[174,1232,676,725]" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">
M a t e r i a l. 
<materialsCitation id="78FC3C85DC12FF15FE911C97FFCDDB92" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3751772302" collectionCode="SIZK" location="Rovno" municipality="Rovno" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" specimenCode="UA-335" specimenCount="1" specimenCount-female="1" typeStatus="holotype">
<typeStatus id="172F887ADC12FF15FE911C97FE8DDBFD" box="[349,442,676,698]" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Holotype</typeStatus>
. Possibly 
<specimenCount id="DE92FD51DC12FF15FDDA1C97FD6FDBFD" box="[534,600,676,698]" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" type="female">female</specimenCount>
, only thorax and elytra present. 
<collectionCode id="AE85AE1DDC12FF15FC471C97FC8ADBFD" box="[907,957,676,698]" country="Ukraine" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/c442-9tdv" name="Schmaulhausen Institute of Zoology" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">SIZK</collectionCode>
<specimenCode id="98329EA3DC12FF15FC0E1C97FB25DBFD" box="[962,1042,676,698]" collectionCode="UA-" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">UA-335</specimenCode>
, 
<collectingMunicipality id="284FACA2DC12FF15FBD61C97FB6DDBFD" box="[1050,1114,676,698]" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Rovno</collectingMunicipality>
amber, 
<geologicalTimeScale id="BAB4B673DC12FF15FB6B1C97FFC1DB92" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Late Eocene</geologicalTimeScale>
.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="808E6553DC12FF15FF2F1CCFFB55DD91" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" type="description">
<paragraph id="C82B36D8DC12FF15FF2F1CCFFB55DD91" blockId="1.[174,1233,763,1717]" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">
D e s c r i p t i o n. Length (pronotum plus elytra): 1.5 mm. Relatively robust, roundedsided; color brownish (
<figureCitation id="50AF2A5DDC12FF15FE751D28FD39DA72" box="[441,526,795,821]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1438,1460]" captionTargetBox="[161,1221,206,1413]" captionTargetId="figure-106@2.[160,780,205,857]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Sucinoptinus from Rovno amber: 1 — Sucinoptinus rovnoensis sp. n. Holotype, SIZK UA-335; 2 — Sucinoptinus brevipennis sp.n. Holotype, SIZK D-2295; 3 — Sucinoptinus sp.? SIZK UA-284; 4 — Sucinoptinus sp.? SIZK K-6067; 5 — Sucinoptinus? sp.? SIZK K-25483; 6 — Rovno amber deposits with Sucinoptinus inclusions: a — Dubrovitsa, b — Klesov. Scale 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6414449" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6414449/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">
fig. 1, 
<emphasis id="FAE0EACADC12FF15FDCC1D28FD39DA72" box="[512,526,795,821]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">1</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). Pronotum slightly wider than long and neatly wider than a single elytron; apical margin widely convex anteriorly; sides only slightly rounded, practically not constricted near the base, moderately convex at the disk and showing a quite apparent semicircular depression in the posterior third; surface covered with dense tubercles, oval and large, specially within the semicircular depression, where they are almost as large as half the size of the scutellum; pubescence formed by short semi-recumbent hairs inserted between the tubercles (
<figureCitation id="50AF2A5DDC12FF15FE7B1DE8FD3CDAB2" box="[439,523,987,1013]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1438,1460]" captionTargetBox="[161,1221,206,1413]" captionTargetId="figure-106@2.[160,780,205,857]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Sucinoptinus from Rovno amber: 1 — Sucinoptinus rovnoensis sp. n. Holotype, SIZK UA-335; 2 — Sucinoptinus brevipennis sp.n. Holotype, SIZK D-2295; 3 — Sucinoptinus sp.? SIZK UA-284; 4 — Sucinoptinus sp.? SIZK K-6067; 5 — Sucinoptinus? sp.? SIZK K-25483; 6 — Rovno amber deposits with Sucinoptinus inclusions: a — Dubrovitsa, b — Klesov. Scale 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6414449" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6414449/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">
fig. 1, 
<emphasis id="FAE0EACADC12FF15FE311DE8FD3CDAB2" box="[509,523,987,1013]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">1</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). Scutellum triangular, as long as wide. Elytra slightly roundsided and relatively short, 1.35 as long as wide, but clearly longer than twice the length of the pronotum; humeri prominent; elytral surface serially punctuated by elongated strial punctures, leaving an interstriae interval about twice wider as the width of the striae; pubescence formed by recumbent short setae inserted in the punctures (with a length somewhat longer that the puncture), semirecumbent and moderately long (somewhat longer than those of the punctures) setae inserted in the intervals and evenly distributed, and erect and still longer setae sparsely distributed in the interstriae of the apical part (
<figureCitation id="50AF2A5DDC12FF15FC371A88FB66DD91" box="[1019,1105,1211,1238]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1438,1460]" captionTargetBox="[161,1221,206,1413]" captionTargetId="figure-106@2.[160,780,205,857]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Sucinoptinus from Rovno amber: 1 — Sucinoptinus rovnoensis sp. n. Holotype, SIZK UA-335; 2 — Sucinoptinus brevipennis sp.n. Holotype, SIZK D-2295; 3 — Sucinoptinus sp.? SIZK UA-284; 4 — Sucinoptinus sp.? SIZK K-6067; 5 — Sucinoptinus? sp.? SIZK K-25483; 6 — Rovno amber deposits with Sucinoptinus inclusions: a — Dubrovitsa, b — Klesov. Scale 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6414449" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6414449/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">
fig. 1, 
<emphasis id="FAE0EACADC12FF15FB8F1A8FFB66DD91" box="[1091,1105,1212,1238]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">1</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="808E6553DC12FF15FF2F1AEFFDC5DF32" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C82B36D8DC12FF15FF2F1AEFFDC5DF32" blockId="1.[174,1233,763,1717]" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">
D i a g n o s t i c c h a r a c t e r s. The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="0F944D5BDC12FF15FC531AEFFB3BDDB2" authorityName="Alexeev" authorityYear="2012" box="[927,1036,1243,1270]" class="Insecta" family="Ptinidae" genus="Sucinoptinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bukejsi">
<emphasis id="FAE0EACADC12FF15FC531AEFFB3BDDB2" box="[927,1036,1243,1270]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">S. bukejsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from amber inclusions found at Yantarny (formerly Palmnicken) in the 
<collectingRegion id="0A50F83ADC12FF15FC851AC8FB1EDC52" box="[841,1065,1275,1301]" country="Russia" name="Kaliningrad" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Kaliningrad region</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="B0837648DC12FF15FBFF1AC8FB48DC52" box="[1075,1151,1275,1301]" name="Russia" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Russia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="AC054B29DC12FF15FB411AC8FE10DC71" author="Alekseev, V. I." pageId="1" pageNumber="18" pagination="145 - 148" refId="ref2880" refString="Alekseev, V. I. 2012. Sucinoptinus bukejsi sp. nov. (Coleoptera: Ptinidae: Ptinini), the second species of the Tertiary genus from the Baltic amber. Baltic Journal of Coleopterology, 12 (2), 145 - 148." type="journal article" year="2012">Alekseev, 2012</bibRefCitation>
) in having the same general structure of pronotum and elytra, but differing from this species by the morphology of the pronotum, with sides only slightly rounded and practically not constricted near the base, whereas that of 
<taxonomicName id="0F944D5BDC12FF15FCEC1B6FFCB9DC32" authorityName="Alexeev" authorityYear="2012" box="[800,910,1371,1398]" class="Insecta" family="Ptinidae" genus="Sucinoptinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bukejsi">
<emphasis id="FAE0EACADC12FF15FCEC1B6FFCB9DC32" box="[800,910,1371,1398]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">S. bukejsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the sides well rounded leaving a slight but clear constriction near the base. Moreover, the semicircular depression of the posterior third of the pronotal disk of 
<taxonomicName id="0F944D5BDC12FF15FD3B1BAFFCBADCF2" authorityName="Bellés &amp; Perkovsky" authorityYear="2016" box="[759,909,1436,1462]" class="Insecta" family="Ptinidae" genus="Sucinoptinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rovnoensis">
<emphasis id="FAE0EACADC12FF15FD3B1BAFFCBADCF2" box="[759,909,1436,1462]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">S. rovnoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not present in 
<taxonomicName id="0F944D5BDC12FF15FB901BAFFBFEDCF2" authorityName="Alexeev" authorityYear="2012" box="[1116,1225,1435,1462]" class="Insecta" family="Ptinidae" genus="Sucinoptinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bukejsi">
<emphasis id="FAE0EACADC12FF15FB901BAFFBFEDCF2" box="[1116,1225,1435,1462]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">S. bukejsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which shows a regularly convex pronotal disk, with a depression in the posterior third only slightly marked. The large tubercles forming the surface of the semicircular depression of 
<taxonomicName id="0F944D5BDC12FF15FF621BCFFE73DF52" authorityName="Bellés &amp; Perkovsky" authorityYear="2016" box="[174,324,1532,1558]" class="Insecta" family="Ptinidae" genus="Sucinoptinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rovnoensis">
<emphasis id="FAE0EACADC12FF15FF621BCFFE73DF52" box="[174,324,1532,1558]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">S. rovnoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are neither present in 
<taxonomicName id="0F944D5BDC12FF15FD9C1BCFFD8ADF52" authorityName="Alexeev" authorityYear="2012" box="[592,701,1531,1558]" class="Insecta" family="Ptinidae" genus="Sucinoptinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bukejsi">
<emphasis id="FAE0EACADC12FF15FD9C1BCFFD8ADF52" box="[592,701,1531,1558]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">S. bukejsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which shows a 
<typeStatus id="172F887ADC12FF15FCB11BCFFC98DF51" box="[893,943,1532,1558]" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">type</typeStatus>
of tubercles smaller and evenly distributed. 
<taxonomicName id="0F944D5BDC12FF15FE43182FFDC6DF71" authority="Belles et Vitali (2007)" authorityName="Belles et Vitali" authorityYear="2007" box="[399,753,1563,1590]" class="Insecta" family="Ptinidae" genus="Sucinoptinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sucini">
<emphasis id="FAE0EACADC12FF15FE43182FFED9DF72" box="[399,494,1564,1590]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">S. sucini</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="AC054B29DC12FF15FE391828FDC6DF71" author="Belles, X. &amp; Vitali, F." box="[501,753,1563,1590]" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" pagination="17 - 28" refId="ref3056" refString="Belles, X., Vitali, F. 2007. New fossil spider beetles from Baltic amber (Coleoptera Ptinidae). Entomapeiron (P. S.), 2 (2), 17 - 28." type="journal article" year="2007">Bellés et Vitali (2007)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
also has a semicircular depression in the posterior third of the pronotal disk, but it is narrower and the tubercles of the sculpture within it are much smaller and rounded in shape.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="808E6553DC12FF15FF2F184FFE7FDFF2" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="C82B36D8DC12FF15FF2F184FFE7FDFF2" blockId="1.[174,1233,763,1717]" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">
E t y m o l o g y. The specific name refers to 
<collectingRegion id="0A50F83ADC12FF15FD2A184FFCBCDFD2" box="[742,907,1659,1686]" country="Ukraine" name="Rivne" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Rovno region</collectingRegion>
, the geographical origin of the 
<typeStatus id="172F887ADC12FF15FF1618A8FE73DFF2" box="[218,324,1691,1717]" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
